headline: FHFA Director To Head Fannie Mae, Freddie Mac Boards Amid Shake-Ups
summary: The FHFA removed eight members from the board of the Federal National Mortgage Association, known as Fannie Mae. The agency additionally culled six members from the board of the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp., or Freddie Mac.

headline: Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac Stocks Fall After Big Climb. Expect More Volatility.
summary: The stocks rallied after the U.S. presidential election as investors saw President Donald Trump’s administration as potentially friendly to removing the companies from conservatorship.
